OL,3,CFormer sub-postmaster says clearing
OL,4,Cname 'overtook' cancer all clear
OL,6,FA Post Office sub-postmaster caught up
OL,7,Fin the Horizon scandal said finding
OL,8,Fout his conviction would be quashed
OL,9,F"overtook" news of being cancer-free
OL,10,F24 hours earlier.
OL,12,FKeith Bell spent his entire life
OL,13,Fsavings of #16,000 to make up the
OL,14,Ffalse shortfall at his Stockton branch
OL,15,Fmore than two decades ago. He was then
OL,16,Fprosecuted and wrongly convicted of
OL,17,Ffalse accounting in 2002.
OL,19,FOn Monday 11 March, Mr Bell was given
OL,20,Fthe all-clear after five years of
OL,21,Fcancer treatment.
